About
Doraemon
Doraemon
is
a
popular
Japanese
manga
and
anime
series
created
by
Fujiko
F.
Fujio.
The
series
revolves
around
a
robotic
cat
named
Doraemon,
who
travels
back
in
time
to
assist
a
clumsy
boy
named
Nobita.
Extend
your
knowledge
of
Doraemon
with
us.

Did
You
Know?
Doraemon
is
often
called
"the
Japanese
Mickey
Mouse".
The
word
"Dora"
in
Doraemon
comes
from
the
word
"doramushi"
(meaning
"mudskipper")
which
is
Nobita's
favorite
animal.
After
Fujiko's
death,
the
series
continued
with
new
mangaka
creating
their
own
versions
of
Doraemon.

Why
Doraemon
Matters
Doraemon
has
been
an
essential
part
of
childhoods
worldwide,
captivating
generations
with
its
fantastic
world
and
beloved
characters.
Its
messages
of
friendship,
perseverance,
and
hard
work
have
inspired
millions
of
kids.
1
Teaches
Values
Doraemon
teaches
children
the
importance
of
honesty,
kindness,
and
teamwork
as
they
go
along
with
the
characters'
day-to-day
adventures.
2
Culture
Bridge
Doraemon
serves
as
a
cultural
exchange
that
bridges
the
gap
for
children
worldwide,
exposing
them
to
various
aspects
of
Japanese
culture,
such
as
its
folklore
and
traditions.
3
Social
Impact
Doraemon
has
been
praised
for
its
positive
social
impact,
such
as
teaching
children
empathy
and
conflict
resolution
and
being
instrumental
in
creating
a
safer
and
more
supportive
school
environment.
